description: Data visualization and chart styling standards
alwaysApply: true
---

## Chart Layout and Structure

- When implementing **any chart or time series visualization**, wrap it in a `div` with class `chart-card` and follow this general structure:
  - `div.chart-card`
    - `div.header` containing a left-aligned title (`.logo`) and a right-aligned secondary action (`.open`).
    - `fieldset.crypto-switch` for switching between series (e.g., BTC/ETH/SOL/TET) using `input[type="radio"]` and `label` pairs, plus a `.slider` element for the animated background.
    - `div.price-infos` containing one or more `.price-info` sections, each with:
      - `.price` (primary metric, e.g., current value)
      - `.stats` with `.amount` and `.change` elements.
    - `div.chart` containing one or more `svg` elements with `path` elements for the chart line.

## Required CSS Pattern

- Charts should reuse or closely follow this **CSS pattern** (class names must match, content can be customized):
  - `.chart-card` for the main card container (dark background, rounded corners, drop shadow).
  - `.header`, `.logo`, `.open` for the header layout and hover interaction.
  - `.crypto-switch`, its `input`/`label` structure, and `.slider` for the segmented switch and animated slider.
  - `.price-infos`, `.price-info`, `.price-info .price`, `.price-info .stats`, `.price-info .change` for the numeric summary.
  - `.chart`, `.chart svg`, `.chart path` with an animated `stroke-dasharray` / `stroke-dashoffset` and `@keyframes draw` to animate the chart line.
  - Use `:has()` selectors on `.chart-card` to toggle which `svg` and `.price-info` are visible based on the checked radio input.

## HTML/CSS Reference Snippet

- Treat the following as the **canonical reference** for how charts should look and behave (you may adapt text, IDs, and values as needed, but keep the structure and class names, using `chart-card` instead of `crypto-card`):

```html
<div class="chart-card">
  <div class="header">
    <span class="logo">CryptoApp</span>
    <span class="open">Open App →</span>
  </div>

  <fieldset class="crypto-switch">
    <input type="radio" id="bitcoin" name="crypto" checked />
    <label for="bitcoin">BTC</label>
    <input type="radio" id="ethereum" name="crypto" />
    <label for="ethereum">ETH</label>
    <input type="radio" id="solana" name="crypto" />
    <label for="solana">SOL</label>
    <input type="radio" id="tether" name="crypto" />
    <label for="tether">TET</label>
    <div class="slider"></div>
  </fieldset>

  <div class="price-infos">
    <!-- .price-info blocks per series -->
  </div>

  <div class="chart">
    <!-- one or more <svg> charts with <path> lines -->
  </div>
</div>
```

- The corresponding CSS (colors, layout, animation) should be **copied or closely mirrored** from the original snippet you provided so that all charts in this project share this same interactive card look and feel.